\begin_layout Plain Layout
All of us are born knowing how to dream, seeing all the wonder and beauty
 of the world.
 So many forget.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Humanity always lived under the shadow of horrors, human and inhuman alike.
 To dream of a better world, to confront the shadows and beat them back
 was always too risky, always too audacious.
 Better to lay low and survive.
 To try for better means to maybe lose what you already have.
 So...
 it is, that we are taught not to dream.
 That is the nature of survival.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
...
 but someone has to try, right? You dreamed even in the darkest of nights,
 knowing that the day will break as always.
 You held your dreams close, never letting the worlds convince you to let
 them go.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Those dreams of better worlds, where humanity triumphs over the trials of
 life.
 In those dreams, you weren't alone.
 You dreamed with others who believed in the same future.
 Just maybe, it wasn't just an passing fantasy.
 Maybe there is more to this world, true meaning in that dream.
 Pushing away the little voice in the corner of your mind, that such things
 are impossible, you clung onto that hope.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Even as the world pushed you into a corner, asked for you to yield...
 you stood.
 When everything was on the line, you refused to break, let the world turn
 you into another cog in the machine.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
In a fleeting moment, you saw that dream again.
 But, this time, you held all its power in your own hands.
 You shaped it into a light to call your own, awakening into an endless
 waking dream.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
With the light of two worlds, just maybe, you could really make a difference.
\end_layout

