\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
Luminous: the Dream
\series default
 is a roleplaying game set in the 
\series bold
Chronicles of Darkness
\series default
, a world much like our own but caught between bleak mundanity and terrifying
 supernatural horrors.
 Night fell long ago, and the humanity still struggles against both the
 supernatural darkness that envelops it and its own faults.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
...
 even in such a world, there is beauty, small lights hidden away in the
 night.
 In the depths of everyone's dreams, paths lead into a grand shared dream.
 Long ago, eight great Dream Kingdoms were imagined within, each an reflection
 of a world that could one day be real.
 A rare few chose to stay, live a second life in those worlds.
 A rarer few found a shining power in themselves, drawing on the light of
 both.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
They are the Luminous.
 In a moment they call their Realization, they all once awoke a power deep
 in their soul.
 Wielding that light, they weave their dreams into reality, taking on the
 form they always imagined.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Their story is not a happy one.
 Every Luminous was once hurt by the world in one way or another; asked
 to stop dreaming so brightly, stop caring so much.
 For all the power they hold, the shadows of the world seem far too vast
 for any one person – magical or otherwise – to fix.
 But they still try.
 Someone has to.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
In the Dream, they feel all the pains and joys of the world as deeply as
 their own.
 A dream so broken, hurt and scarred by all that had happened.
 Alongside the idyllic forests and shining cities, our pains and sorrows
 reflect just as clearly in humanity's Dream.
 Even there, the light is fleeting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Maybe that's okay.
 In time, even such a world can be healed, brick by brick, dream by dream
 and person by person.
 That is the task that falls to the Luminous.
\end_layout

