\begin_layout Subsection*
Crossing Paths
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Every person in the world has their own colorful lives to live, all woven
 together into one whole.
 Everyone relies on another, has been hurt by another, loves another.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Luminous is a game about those connections, and the chance encounters that
 create them.
 They rely on each other for hope when things are too dark for them to stand
 alone.
 Through their magic of dreams, they come to understand and rely on the
 very different people and supernatural creatures they share a world with.
 Shining together as a constellation, they can achieve things they could
 never alone.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Lights and Shadows
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
For all its flaws, the world still has its bright places, hidden among the
 shadows.
 For all its problems, the world is still beautiful.
 Little shops in the corner full of life, gardens tucked away between the
 city blocks...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
It's all to think life nothing but suffering.
 It's easier to accept how the world is, if you pretend there's no point
 in trying for better.
 It's all too easy to bury your head in the sand, and pretend survival is
 living.
 But, someone who doesn't see the world as it is won't see the hidden beauty
 hidden in plain sight.
 To see the world as it is means to accept all of it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
The Cost of Hope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
To survive always comes at the cost of hope.
 Trying to make things better for yourself and those you love always risks
 what you already have.
 You can only help so many people before you don't have enough for yourself.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
In holding on hope anyway, the Luminous risk all they already have.
 They fight a battle that is meant to be hopeless; so that people don't
 dare to dream.
 They fight in the name those they care about, in a world that expects people
 to keep their heads down so they aren't next in line.
 Just maybe, one day, they will turn the tides.
 That is what it means to hope.
\end_layout

